        <h1>Admin Help: Viewing Data in the System</h1>
        <p>Welcome, Admin! This guide will help you understand how to view the various records and data in the system.</p>

        <h2>View Admins:</h2>
        <p>To view the list of Admins in the system:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Go to the "Admin Management" section in the main menu.</li>
            <li>Here you will see a table displaying all registered admins with their details.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>View Accounts:</h2>
        <p>To view user accounts:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Navigate to the "Accounts" section from the admin dashboard.</li>
            <li>You can see all registered user accounts, including details like username and account status.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>View Teachers:</h2>
        <p>To view the list of Teachers:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Go to the "Teacher Management" section.</li>
            <li>A table of teachers with their respective details such as name, email, and classes taught will be shown.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>View Parents:</h2>
        <p>To view Parents and their details:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Select "Parent Management" from the menu.</li>
            <li>Here, you can see a list of all parents associated with students, along with their contact information.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>View Students:</h2>
        <p>To view the list of Students:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Go to the "Student Management" section.</li>
            <li>A table will display students, including their names, grade levels, and associated parent information.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>View Attendance Records:</h2>
        <p>To view attendance records:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Go to the "Attendance Records" section in the admin dashboard.</li>
            <li>You can search and filter records by student name, date, or class to view attendance details.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
